**â€œCreate an elegant, emotional, high-end digital poster to celebrate Vietnamese Teachersâ€™ Day (20/11).
Theme: Deep gratitude and respect for teachers, symbolizing the role of educators as guides who illuminate the path of knowledge for students.
Target audience: middle-school students (TrÆ°á»ng THCS Chu VÄƒn An â€“ Cáº©m Pháº£, Quáº£ng Ninh), school environment, Vietnamese culture.
The poster must be artistic, meaningful, modern, and suitable for an official school celebration eventâ€”no childish style.
â€” Visual Concept â€”
Main scene centered around the symbolic relationship between teacher and student:
â€¢ A warm golden light emerging from an open book, forming into a soft silhouette of a teacher gently guiding students.
â€¢ Students standing in awe, looking toward the light with admiration and gratitude.
â€¢ The teacher figure should NOT be a realistic portrait; instead use silhouette, soft illustration, or semi-abstract forms to maintain elegance and avoid uncanny results.
â€¢ Integrate Vietnamese cultural elements subtly: lotus petals, gentle sunlight at dawn, chalk dust texture, school corridor lines, yellow-tiled classical school windows, notebook grid pattern (káº» Ã´ ly) layered faintly in the background.
â€¢ Artistic tone: emotional, calm, inspiring, respectful. Avoid anything chaotic or overly futuristic.
â€” Style & Art Direction â€”
â€¢ Premium minimalist graphic design.
â€¢ Warm, cinematic lighting with smooth gradients.
â€¢ Ultra-clean composition; clear hierarchy; empty space for typography.
â€¢ Background: deep navy blue (#0B3D91) with subtle paper-texture ivory highlights (#FFF8F0).
â€¢ Accent colors: gold (#D4AF37), soft white, gentle warm yellow.
â€¢ Subtle bokeh lights, soft rays, or floating particles representing knowledge and inspiration.
