2.	Bayesian updates â€” update priors to posteriors when evidence arrives.
VN: cáº­p nháº­t niá»m tin theo dá»¯ liá»‡u má»›i.
Anchor: Bayesian brain account (Knill & Pouget).
3.	Hierarchical information flow â€” processing in layers (lowâ†’high abstractions).
VN: xá»­ lÃ½ tá»« chi tiáº¿t lÃªn khÃ¡i quÃ¡t.
4.	Working memory (WM) â€” short-term workspace (limited slots).
VN: â€œRAMâ€ tÆ° duy; háº¡n cháº¿ sá»‘ bÆ°á»›c giá»¯ cÃ¹ng lÃºc.
