The TÃ y people, also known as the ThÃ¡i, are the largest ethnic minority group in Vietnam, with about 1.7 million people.
They mainly live in the northern mountainous provinces such as Cao Bang, Lang Son, Ha Giang, Thai Nguyen, and Lao Cai.
The TÃ y people came from ancient Tai groups in southern China and moved to Vietnam a long time ago.
They have a rich culture with traditional festivals, music, and handicrafts.
